text: Kälarne IK is a sports club in Kälarne in Sweden. It was established on 14 February 1920. The women's soccer team played in the Swedish top division in 1978. Other famous people are track and field athletes Henry Kälarne and Gunder Hägg as well as cross-country skier Alfred Dahlqvist. At different occasions they all have competed for the club.KIK förr, accessdate: 14 October 2013 ==References== ==Other websites== *Official website Category:1920 establishments in Sweden Category:Swedish football clubs Category:Ski clubs in Sweden
